The low-carb, high-fat diet, topped the list of most searched health-related questions on Google this year. In Keto diet, carbohydrate intake is reduced and it is replaced with fats. The reduction on carbs puts the body in a metabolic state called Ketosis, in which body burns fat for energy. This diet has been proven very beneficial in weight loss and has numerous other health benefits. Apart from this, Keto diet also improves your skin and helps with the polycystic ovarian syndrome (PCOS).

Amyotrophic lateral sclerosis or ALS is the second most searched health related question on Google. The disease possibly generated curiosity among people after the death of physicist Stephen Hawking in March. This nervous system disease attacks nerve cells in your brain and spinal cord, which is responsible for controlling voluntary muscle movement. Hawking was diagnosed with this condition when he was 21, but he lived with it for more than 50 years, which is a very long time for a person suffering from this condition.

Flu is not only the most common disease, but it is also even contagious of all. Studies say that if a person has flu, they are contagious for about a week after falling sick. Also one falls sick two to four days after being infected. You can go for a flu shot to protect yourself from this.

According to a report in CNN, implantation bleeding is the seventh most searched question. Implantation bleeding generally occurs in early pregnancy, mostly between 6 and 12 days after conception. It happens when the fertilised egg attaches to the lining of the uterus and is often mistaken as a regular period cycle as it looks similar. It is generally light and short and happens for a few days.

The burning sensation in the middle of the chest, near the heart, is called as heartburn, which is the ninth most searched question. It is nowhere related to heart but is rather a condition of stomach and esophagus. It occurs when the stomach acid flows back into the esophagus and leads to a burning sensation.
